RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 83. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 18 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since August 18 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Races Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). Oklahoma Bred Claiming Price $17,500. (If management deems it necessary to take this race off the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlong on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIRDIE BE GONE was settled and saving ground into the turn, rallied and moved out to be three wide in the stretch, was in a strong drive to take command then was able to hold sway in the final stride. PRETTY IN PINK was unhurried early on then saved ground on the turn, rallied in upper stretch two wide then moved out in mid stretch to be five wide in late stretch and was gaining ground but just missed in the end. TAY TAY'S BABY was unhurried early then rallied and was five wide in the stretch, was gaining ground and finished well. FOR FUN was allowed to settled then rallied and was six wide in the stretch, was gaining ground but was out finished. HOT TUB HOTTIE dueled for the lead while two wide, was in a long drive in the stretch but weakened in late stretch. HEATIN UP chased the early pace while four wide into the turn, made a bid then was no menace in late stretch. MY GOLDEN BLING was unhurried earl and failed to menace. MISSISZIPPY BLING chased the early pace while three wide, was used up then gave way. BLAME IT ON MAMIE dueled for the lead while inside, was hard used then stopped in the stretch drive. FROSTY BREW chased the early pace while four wide into the turn, was used up then stopped.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 3 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 18, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since August 18 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HUNTER QUICK was allowed to settled on the backstretch, rallied on the far turn while two wide, was in a strong drive and powered to the front then held sway in the end. HIT ONE OUT was unhurried early then rallied on the far turn, was three wide in the stretch and gaining ground to finished well. SEDARIS was allowed to settled while inside, rallied on the far turn and was two wide in the stretch but hung in late stretch. SWEET BAKER set the early pace and drew off on the backstretch, was in a long drive then weakened in late stretch. CHARING CROSS was unhurried early then failed to menace in the stretch. LASTCALLFORALCOHOL was outrun and no threat. HOODOO BROWN was unruly in the gate and reared up at the start, lost his rider then was walked off. A steward's inquiry was held concerning the start. After reviewing the film's, no action was taken.
